Welcome to the Amplafi opensource tools project. The goal of this
project is to get a user up and running with all of the needed tools and
source to work on the opensource projects.


Note: at the moment this document will have a unix slant.


1.	#Prerequisites:#
	* <a href="https://github.com/"><b>A Github Account:</b></a>
		* Setup your machine to use github with their <a
				href="http://help.github.com/set-up-git-redirect">instructions</a>.
		* <a href="http://help.github.com/fork-a-repo/">Fork</a> the
			project that you will be working on to your github account.
		
		
	* <a href="http://help.github.com/set-up-git-redirect"><b>Git
		1.7+:</b></a> the program git is needed for the initial download and install.
		* Check this is installed by typing <b>git --version</b> in
			the console.
		* The ouput should say something like: git version 1.7.
		* Use the <a href="http://help.github.com/set-up-git-redirect">instructions</a>
			if you need to set it up. If you get an error like: <i>Permission
			denied (publickey)</i>. Then you didn't properly follow the instructions,
			set up your SSH key now.
		
	* <a
			href="http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html"><b>Java
		JDK 1.6+:</b></a> this program is needed to run builds.
		* Check that this is installed by typing <b>java -version</b>
			in the console.
		* The output should say something like: Java SE runtime build
			1.6.
	* <a href="http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/"><b>Eclipse
		latest download:</b></a> This is the tool you will be developing in.
		*The "Eclipse IDE for Java EE Developers" is the tool you
			need.</li>

	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>
	<h2>Creating the proper folder structure.</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Find the place where you want the amplafi files and tools to
		be placed.</li>
		<li>Create the amplafi-code directory.</li>
	</ol>
	</li>
	<li>
	<h2>Cloning the amplafi-tools repository using git.</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Run this command #&gt; <b>git clone
		https://github.com/amplafi/amplafi-tools.git</b>
	</ol>
	</li>
	<li>
	<h2>Starting the ant script.</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>cd into the amplafi-tools directory.</li>
		<li>run this command #&gt; <b>apache-ant-1.8.2/bin/ant
		opensource-one-time-setup</b></li>
		<li>The console window will ask prompt for things so pay
		attention and answer the questions/promts.</li>
		<li>If the build fails then read the error and see if is
		something easy like github not being setup properly. Then fix that and
		rerun the command.</li>
	</ol>
	</li>
	<li>
	<h2>Setup the Eclipse workspace.</h2>
	Now that you have the opensource files it is time to add them to an
	Eclipse workspace.
	<ol>
		<li>Open eclipse and set your working directory to the
		amplafi-code directory.</li>
		<li>Go to the workbench.</li>
		<li>use the menu <b>File&gt;Import...</b></li>
		<li>open the General folder (with the + sign or arrow) and select
		<b>Existing Projects Into Workspace</b>.</li>
		<li>Hit the next button.</li>
		<li>On the option <b>Select root directory</b> hit the browse
		button.</li>
		<li>Choose the <b>amplafi-code</b> directory(and hit okay).</li>
		<li>A list of projects should appear on the screen, and all of
		them should be checked.</li>
		<li>Now, hit <b>Finish</b>.</li>
		<li>Now, eclipse will take a moment and refresh and build the
		projects. When it completes you should see no errors (just warnings
		and tasks).</li>
		<li>If you see errors, then close eclipse and:
		<ol>
			<li>, go to the command window and run this command again #&gt;
			<b>apache-ant-1.8.2/bin/ant opensource-one-time-setup</b></li>
			<li>Open eclipse to the amplafi-code workspace.</li>
			<li>Select all of the projects on the left hand side and <b>press
			the F5 key</b> (This will force the re).</li>
			<li>Now use the menu <b>Projects&gt;clean...</b></li>
			<li>Choose <b>clean all projects</b>.</li>
			<li>If the errors still don't go away after the rebuild then ask
			for help.</li>
		</ol>
		</li>
	</ol>
	</li>
	<li>
	<h2>Configure Eclipse</h2>
	The following files are located in the src/main/resources/eclipse/
	directory.
	<ol>
		<li>import the eclipse-java-codetemplates.xml
		<ul>
			<li>Use the menu <b>Window&gt;Preferences&gt; ---
			Java&gt;Code Style&gt;Code Templates</b></li>
		</ul>
		</li>
		<li>import the eclipse-java-formatting.xml
		<ul>
			<li>Use the menu <b>Window&gt;Preferences&gt; ---
			Java&gt;Code Style&gt;Formatter</b></li>
		</ul>
		</li>
		<li>import the eclipse-java-cleanup.xml
		<ul>
			<li>Use the menu <b>Window&gt;Preferences&gt; ---
			Java&gt;Code Style&gt;Clean Up</b></li>
		</ul>
		</li>
		<li>import the eclipse.bookmarks.xml
		<ul>
			<li>TODO: how is this added? Is this needed for the opensource
			code?</li>
		</ul>
		</li>

		<li>import the eclipse.importorder
		<ul>
			<li>TODO: how is this added? Is this needed for the opensource
			code?</li>
		</ul>
		</li>
	</ol>
	</li>
	<li>Fork</li>
</ol>
